{"word":"H4124 - מֹואָב - Môwʼâb - mo-awb - Moab","slug":"H4124","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">מֹואָב</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>Môwʼâb"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>mo-awb"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Moab"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05DE;&#x05D5;&#x05D0;&#x05D1; - mo&#x0302;'a&#x0302;b</b> - <i>mo-awb</i><p/>From a prolonged form of the prepositional prefix <i>&ldquo;m-&rdquo;</i> and <a href=\"#/H1\">H1</a>; <i>from</i> (her (the mother&rsquo;s)) <i>father</i>; <i>Moab</i>, an incestuous son of Lot; also his territory and descendants: - Moab."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H4125\">H4125</a>"}]}